  <body>
    <div style="basic">
        <p begin="00:00:00.000" end="00:00:06.200" tts:direction="ltr">Hello, visitors and welcome to your first
<br />Data 5,400 challenge.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:06.200" end="00:00:07.960" tts:direction="ltr">This challenge will focus on</p>
        <p begin="00:00:07.960" end="00:00:12.720" tts:direction="ltr">the base camp learnings of purpose,
<br />audience, and credibility.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:12.720" end="00:00:17.120" tts:direction="ltr">I'm excited for you to jump in this
<br />applied assignment,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:17.120" end="00:00:20.200" tts:direction="ltr">and let's take a look at the prompt.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:20.200" end="00:00:22.560" tts:direction="ltr">The question I'm offering you is can you</p>
        <p begin="00:00:22.560" end="00:00:26.960" tts:direction="ltr">communicate the right data to the right
<br />audience in the right way?</p>
        <p begin="00:00:26.960" end="00:00:30.800" tts:direction="ltr">When was the last time you Googled blank
<br />near me,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:30.800" end="00:00:33.080" tts:direction="ltr">whether that be restaurants near me,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:33.080" end="00:00:34.760" tts:direction="ltr">mattress stores near me,</p>
        <p begin="00:00:34.760" end="00:00:37.280" tts:direction="ltr">gas stations near me or dog parks.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:37.280" end="00:00:42.520" tts:direction="ltr">Your task assigned to you by a state
<br />planning commission is to figure out</p>
        <p begin="00:00:42.520" end="00:00:44.760" tts:direction="ltr">what people over the last year in</p>
        <p begin="00:00:44.760" end="00:00:49.760" tts:direction="ltr">your chosen state are looking for near me
<br />rising searches.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:49.760" end="00:00:54.420" tts:direction="ltr">We will use Google trends to gather this
<br />live data.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:54.420" end="00:00:59.080" tts:direction="ltr">Let's distill this down into one single
<br />sentence purpose.</p>
        <p begin="00:00:59.080" end="00:01:02.480" tts:direction="ltr">The purpose of this challenge is to
<br />analyze</p>
        <p begin="00:01:02.480" end="00:01:06.560" tts:direction="ltr">rising near me searches in a chosen state
<br />over</p>
        <p begin="00:01:06.560" end="00:01:09.880" tts:direction="ltr">the past year using Google trends to</p>
        <p begin="00:01:09.880" end="00:01:14.440" tts:direction="ltr">uncover what people are increasingly
<br />seeking in their local areas.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:14.440" end="00:01:17.680" tts:direction="ltr">This is important because state planning
<br />commissioners</p>
        <p begin="00:01:17.680" end="00:01:19.200" tts:direction="ltr">are trying to figure out</p>
        <p begin="00:01:19.200" end="00:01:25.015" tts:direction="ltr">what funds they can apply to help
<br />accelerate growth within their state.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:25.015" end="00:01:30.790" tts:direction="ltr">Now, the twist of this challenge is that
<br />you are going to communicate to</p>
        <p begin="00:01:30.790" end="00:01:34.190" tts:direction="ltr">the right audience and that includes</p>
        <p begin="00:01:34.190" end="00:01:38.110" tts:direction="ltr">a persona that we've identified in the
<br />base camp.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:38.110" end="00:01:44.190" tts:direction="ltr">Your crew is assigned one of these five
<br />different personas,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:44.190" end="00:01:46.710" tts:direction="ltr">a thinker, a charismatic,</p>
        <p begin="00:01:46.710" end="00:01:50.910" tts:direction="ltr">a skeptic, a controller, or a follower.</p>
        <p begin="00:01:50.910" end="00:01:53.670" tts:direction="ltr">Make sure that when you are presenting</p>
        <p begin="00:01:53.670" end="00:01:57.950" tts:direction="ltr">that you are looking through the lens of
<br />that profile.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:01.070" end="00:02:03.950" tts:direction="ltr">Now, when it comes to the details,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:03.950" end="00:02:06.350" tts:direction="ltr">you will pick a US state,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:06.350" end="00:02:11.165" tts:direction="ltr">but you won't pick Utah because I'm using
<br />that in the demo.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:11.165" end="00:02:14.620" tts:direction="ltr">Then you will find the appropriate
<br />datasets.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:14.620" end="00:02:17.460" tts:direction="ltr">There will be five sheets that you will
<br />download.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:17.460" end="00:02:19.940" tts:direction="ltr">You will create three charts,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:19.940" end="00:02:22.460" tts:direction="ltr">record a three to five minute video with</p>
        <p begin="00:02:22.460" end="00:02:26.100" tts:direction="ltr">the first half presenting directly to your
<br />audience.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:26.100" end="00:02:29.980" tts:direction="ltr">Now, I know that this might feel a bit
<br />uncomfortable,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:29.980" end="00:02:32.860" tts:direction="ltr">but lean into that uncomfortableness to</p>
        <p begin="00:02:32.860" end="00:02:36.540" tts:direction="ltr">practice presenting to various audiences.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:36.540" end="00:02:38.340" tts:direction="ltr">Make sure you have a clear purpose,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:38.340" end="00:02:40.540" tts:direction="ltr">you're addressing data credibility,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:40.540" end="00:02:42.220" tts:direction="ltr">and you're providing insights.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:42.220" end="00:02:43.980" tts:direction="ltr">The second half of this video,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:43.980" end="00:02:45.860" tts:direction="ltr">you'll describe your process,</p>
        <p begin="00:02:45.860" end="00:02:49.060" tts:direction="ltr">what did you learn in any roadblocks.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:49.060" end="00:02:54.660" tts:direction="ltr">You'll submit that to Canvas and receive
<br />peer feedback.</p>
        <p begin="00:02:54.660" end="00:03:00.110" tts:direction="ltr">You will have the opportunity then to
<br />resubmit if you so choose.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:00.110" end="00:03:06.160" tts:direction="ltr">Now, let's make sure that you understand
<br />what Google Trends is all about.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:06.160" end="00:03:11.120" tts:direction="ltr">Each data point that you see is divided by
<br />the total searches of</p>
        <p begin="00:03:11.120" end="00:03:13.320" tts:direction="ltr">the geography and time range it</p>
        <p begin="00:03:13.320" end="00:03:16.560" tts:direction="ltr">represents compared to the relative
<br />popularity.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:16.560" end="00:03:21.240" tts:direction="ltr">Otherwise, places with the most search
<br />volume would always be ranked highest.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:21.240" end="00:03:24.400" tts:direction="ltr">When you are seeing a number like 75,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:24.400" end="00:03:29.080" tts:direction="ltr">it's not 75 individuals with that search
<br />term.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:29.080" end="00:03:34.955" tts:direction="ltr">Instead, they're using this equation to
<br />determine the popularity.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:34.955" end="00:03:39.310" tts:direction="ltr">So the resulting numbers are then scaled
<br />on a range of zero to</p>
        <p begin="00:03:39.310" end="00:03:44.670" tts:direction="ltr">100 based on a topic's proportion to all
<br />the searches on those topics.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:44.670" end="00:03:48.150" tts:direction="ltr">Different regions that show the same
<br />search interest for</p>
        <p begin="00:03:48.150" end="00:03:52.790" tts:direction="ltr">a term don't always have the same total
<br />search volumes.</p>
        <p begin="00:03:54.160" end="00:03:58.720" tts:direction="ltr">For this challenge, think the higher the
<br />proportion value,</p>
        <p begin="00:03:58.720" end="00:04:02.800" tts:direction="ltr">the more popular the search term
<br />relatively.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:02.800" end="00:04:05.760" tts:direction="ltr">Let's dive into the Google demo</p>
        <p begin="00:04:05.760" end="00:04:09.080" tts:direction="ltr">so that we can get a better sense of how
<br />to download our data.</p>
        <p begin="00:04:09.080" end="00:04:15.440" tts:direction="ltr">I'm in a new browser here and I'm just
